text: Sonkajärvi is a municipality of Finland. It is in the province of Eastern Finland and is part of the Northern Savonia region. The municipality was founded in 1922. In August 2013, 4,596 people lived there. ==Other websites== * The official Sonkajärvi page , in Finnish Category:Municipalities of North Savo Category:1922 establishments in Europe Category:1920s establishments in Finland
